<SECOND>AM-Quadruple Slaying,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shooting, Kidnapping, Chase Leave 5 Dead in West Germany</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFURT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men who may have escaped from
a prison in Austria shot and killed four men in a German bar,
kidnapped a woman, and led police on a chase that ended in a
shootout that left one of the gunmen dead.
   The crime spree began Saturday when the two gunmen killed four
men at a bar in the Bavarian town of Laaber and wounded two others
after demanding money from them, said police Sunday.
   Police said the gunmen, believed to be convicted robbers who
escaped from an Austrian prison, fled in a car that had been stolen
in Austria.
   In the 185-mile chase that followed, the gunmen escaped from a
garage where police had cornered them and kidnapped a 26-year-old
woman from her home near Neumarkt, Bavaria, escaping in her car,
police said.
   Hans Kuffer, spokesman for Hesse state police, said police
finally caught up with the assailants late Saturday south of
Frankfurt.
   One of the gunmen died in a resulting shootout with Bavarian and
Hesse state police, and the other was wounded, Kuffer said.
   He said the woman hostage was not hurt.
