<FIRST>u i AM-Hungary-Mindszenty     11-19 0190</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Hungary-Mindszenty,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>First Memorial In Hungary to Catholic Leader Jailed by Communists</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first memorial to Cardinal Jozsef
Mindszenty, who was convicted of treason in a Stalinist show trial
in the 1940s, was dedicated Sunday in a western village, the state
news agency MTI reported.
   The monument _ two crosses carved out of a block of stone _ was
placed in outside a church in the village of Nemesgulacs that
Mindszenty had founded.
   Following a memorial Mass, church and other representatives met
in the village cultural center to discuss Mindszenty's historical
role, MTI said.
   The Roman Catholic primate was arrested in 1948 and sentenced a
year later to life in prison for treason after confessing to most
of the charges against him. Earlier this month, prosecutors
determined that the confession was illegally coerced, presumably
under duress or drugs.
   He was freed during the 1956 popular uprising and took refuge in
the U.S. Embassy. The uprising was crushed by Soviet tanksn.
   In 1971, the Vatican arranged for his departure from Hungary. He
was removed as primate in 1974. He died a year later at age 83.
